<paragraph id="8BE236E9476D4D089BE2FB84FE1BFBD1" blockId="16.[160,1156,1049,1491]" box="[160,394,1049,1075]" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D089BE2FB84FE1BFBD1" bold="true" box="[160,394,1049,1075]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">Taxonomic remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE236E9476D4D089BE2FBA1FBA8FA31" blockId="16.[160,1156,1049,1491]" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A476D4D089BE2FBA1FE0CFBB7" authorityName="Howden and Young" authorityYear="1981" box="[160,413,1084,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoratus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D089BE2FBA1FE0CFBB7" box="[160,413,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">Dichotomius femoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was formerly identified by its distinctive pattern of microsculpture on the elytral interstriae, which appears to be shagreened near striae and smooth medially. However, the examination of the type material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A476D4D089825FB1FFC74FB79" baseAuthorityName="Felsche" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[871,997,1154,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globulus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D089825FB1FFC74FB79" box="[871,997,1154,1179]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">D. globulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has revealed that some specimens have a very similar pattern of elytral microsculpture to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A476D4D089BE2FB5AFEBCFB02" authorityName="Howden and Young" authorityYear="1981" box="[160,301,1223,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoratus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D089BE2FB5AFEBCFB02" box="[160,301,1223,1248]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">D. femoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The type material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A476D4D089969FB5AFD37FB02" baseAuthorityName="Felsche" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[555,678,1223,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globulus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D089969FB5AFD37FB02" box="[555,678,1223,1248]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">D. globulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of 
<specimenCount id="9D5BFD60476D4D089827FB5AFC41FB02" box="[869,976,1223,1248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
(
<typeStatus id="54E6884B476D4D08989CFB5AFBDBFB02" box="[990,1098,1223,1248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">lectotype</typeStatus>
) and 
<specimenCount id="9D5BFD60476D4D089BE2FB77FEBBFAE1" box="[160,298,1258,1283]" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" type="female">four females</specimenCount>
(
<typeStatus id="54E6884B476D4D089A77FB77FE71FAE1" box="[309,480,1258,1283]" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
). All females have the surface of the elytral interstriae shining at centre and shagreened along the lateral portions near striae, whereas the male has almost the entire surface of interstriae shagreened, with at most scattered smooth dots on the medial portion. To distinguish females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A476D4D0899E0FACFFCBFFA89" authorityName="Howden and Young" authorityYear="1981" box="[674,814,1362,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoratus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D0899E0FACFFCBFFA89" box="[674,814,1362,1387]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">D. femoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A476D4D089895FACFFBC0FA89" baseAuthorityName="Felsche" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[983,1105,1362,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globulus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D089895FACFFBC0FA89" box="[983,1105,1362,1387]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">D. globulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the following characters can be used: body elongate (globose in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A476D4D08980FFAE9FC56FA6F" baseAuthorityName="Felsche" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[845,967,1396,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globulus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D08980FFAE9FC56FA6F" box="[845,967,1396,1421]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">D. globulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) surface of frons and genae with scattered ocellate punctures (
<figureCitation id="13662A6C476D4D08999BFA0AFCAEFA52" box="[729,831,1431,1456]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[160,226,1467,1490]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1432]" captionTargetId="figure-3@6.[163,1153,142,1435]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Detailed morphology of the species in the globulus group. (a) Ventral view of male, Dichotomius femoratus; (b) ventral view of male, D. gamboaensis; (c) male head, D. fortepunctatus; (d) female head, D. gamboaensis; (e) pronotum of male, D. femoratus; (f) pronotum of male, D. fortepunctatus; (g) elytral striae of male, D. fortepunctatus; (h) elytral striae (Estria) of male (ShMicro, shagreened microsculpture), D. femoratus; (i) elytral striae of male, D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (j) male abdominal ventrites in ventral view, D. berthalutzae sp. nov.; (k) male abdominal ventrites in ventral view, D. femoratus; (l) female abdominal ventrites in lateral view, D. femoratus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530258" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530258/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(d)) (densely distributed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A476D4D089BE2FA27FE8BFA31" baseAuthorityName="Felsche" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[160,282,1466,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globulus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D089BE2FA27FE8BFA31" box="[160,282,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">D. globulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and pronotal punctures irregularly spaced (umbilicate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D6A476D4D0898F3FA27FBBDFA31" baseAuthorityName="Felsche" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[945,1068,1466,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globulus">
<emphasis id="B929EAFB476D4D0898F3FA27FBBDFA31" box="[945,1068,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="135">D. globulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
